-- Nigeria's Bauchi State seeks approval to raise 15 bln naira bond
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 11:27AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Nigeria's northeastern state of Bauchi is seeking approval to raise 15 billion naira ($92.05 million) in bonds to fund  development projects, the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) said on Tuesday.

The SEC said Bauchi state meant to use the funds to finance the completion of an airport and a specialist hospital and to refinance existing bank loans, it said in a notice.